hout a peep on it, I thought it silly to pay ","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":2213},"end":{"line":11,"column":255,"offset":2467}}},{"type":"text","value":"$","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":255,"offset":2467},"end":{"line":11,"column":257,"offset":2469}}},{"type":"text","value":"5 a month on something I don’t use. After my free trial of Amazon AWS expired I decided to leave Ghost behind (maybe just until a free tier hosting opened up or I piggy-backed it on another node server).","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":257,"offset":2469},"end":{"line":11,"column":460,"offset":2672}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":2213},"end":{"line":11,"column":460,"offset":2672}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"That’s when a friend introduced me to ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":2674},"end":{"line":13,"column":39,"offset":2712}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://postach.io/sites/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Postach.io","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":40,"offset":2713},"end":{"line":13,"column":50,"offset":2723}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":39,"offset":2712},"end":{"line":13,"column":54,"offset":2727}}},{"type":"text","value":", which changed the way I thought about posting content. Postach.io lets you use Evernote (or Dropbox) as your CMS, simply by placing post-notes in a specified notebook and tagging them as a “post”. They would just magically show up in your blog! Since I already wrote most of my drafts for posts in Evernote, and Postach.io was a dream come true! Sure it was super limiting, but that is exactly what I wanted! And, as if having a great tool at your disposal wasn’t enough, service was free with a premium tier for features I didn’t need. ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":54,"offset":2727},"end":{"line":13,"column":593,"offset":3266}}},{"type":"ele